<odoo>
    <template id="page_odr_standards" name="ODR standards and ethics">
        <t t-call="website.layout">
            <div id="wrap">
                <t t-set="bn_nav_inner" t-value="True"/>
                <t t-call="bharatnyay_website.bn_public_nav"/>
                <div class="bn-about-page">
                    <header class="bn-about-hero text-lg-start bn-hero-split">
                        <div class="container">
                            <p class="bn-hash mb-3">Education · Governance</p>
                            <h1><span class="text-orange">Standards</span> safeguarding ODR legitimacy</h1>
                            <p class="mx-lg-0">Legitimacy stems from neutrality, impartiality, data minimisation, informed consent about recording, multilingual fairness, grievance escalation for unethical neutrals —
                                BharatNyay’s controls echo ICODR &amp; NCTDR-aligned guidance distilled for deployments on regulated balance sheets.</p>
                        </div>
                    </header>
                    <section class="bn-about-body">
                        <div class="container bn-prose bn-prose-wide">
                            <div class="row gy-5">
                                <div class="col-md-6">
                                    <h2>Operational safeguards</h2>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Segregation of duties across recovery desks / legal / neutrals.</li>
                                        <li>Immutable chatter + downloadable audit packs for supervisory examination.</li>
                                        <li>Least-privilege access to personally identifiable borrower data.</li>
                                        <li>Vendor due diligence artefacts for outsourced transcription / hosting.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                                <div class="col-md-6">
                                    <h2>Neutral-facing ethics cues</h2>
                                    <ul>
                                        <li>Conflict disclosures before appointment acceptance.</li>
                                        <li>Fee transparency &amp; pass-through disbursement logs.</li>
                                        <li>Record retention aligned with Evidence Act adaptations for e-records.</li>
                                        <li>No ex-parte caucus bleed into tribunal deliberations improperly.</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                            <hr class="my-5 opacity-25"/>

                            <h2 class="h4 fw-bold mb-3">Protocols &amp; procedural library</h2>
                            <p class="text-muted">Deep dives mirroring layered standards and protocol libraries used by mature ODR platforms and institutional ADR programs.</p>
